Description: The current ETag of the resource.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a string that is defined by the ETag HTTP header definition in RFC7232.

Description: The available actions for this resource.
Normative Description: The Actions property shall contain the available actions for this resource.

Description: The array of physical port references that this network device function may be assigned to.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be an array of physical port references that this network device function may be assigned to.

Description: The boot mode configured for this network device function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the boot mode configured for this network device function.  If the value is not quot;Disabled", this network device function shall be configured for boot using the specified technology.

Description: Provides a description of this resource and is used for commonality  in the schema definitions.
Normative Description: This object represents the Description property.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification.

Description: Whether the network device function is enabled.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether the network device function is enabled.  Disabled network device functions shall not be enumerated or seen by the operating system.

Description: Ethernet.
Normative Description: This object shall contain Ethernet capabilities, status, and configuration values for this network device function.

Description: This is the currently configured MAC address of the (logical port) network device function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the effective current MAC Address of this network device function. If an assignable MAC address is not supported, this is a read only alias of the PermanentMACAddress.

Description: The Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) configured for this network device function.
Normative Description: The Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) configured for this Network Device Function.  This value serves as a default for the OS driver when booting.  The value only takes-effect on boot.

Description: This is the permanent MAC address assigned to this network device function (physical function).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the Permanent MAC Address of this network device function (physical function). This value is typically programmed during the manufacturing time. This address is not assignable.

Description: Fibre Channel.
Normative Description: This object shall contain Fibre Channel capabilities, status, and configuration values for this network device function.

Description: Whether the FCoE Initialization Protocol (FIP) is used for populating the FCoE VLAN Id.
Normative Description: For FCoE connections, the value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether the FIP VLAN Discovery Protocol is used to determine the FCoE VLAN ID selected by the network device function for the FCoE connection.  If true, and the FIP VLAN Discovery succeeds, the FCoEActiveVLANId property shall reflect the FCoE VLAN ID to be used for all FCoE traffic.  If false, or if the FIP VLAN Discovery protocol fails, the FCoELocalVLANId shall be used for all FCoE traffic and the FCoEActiveVLANId shall reflect the FCoELocalVLANId.

Description: An array of Fibre Channel boot targets configured for this network device function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be an array of Fibre Channel boot targets configured for this network device function.

Description: The relative priority for this entry in the boot targets array.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the relative priority for this entry in the boot targets array.  Lower numbers shall represent higher priority, with zero being the highest priority.  The BootPriority shall be unique for all entries of the BootTargets array.

Description: The Logical Unit Number (LUN) ID to boot from on the device referred to by the corresponding WWPN.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the Logical Unit Number (LUN) ID to boot from on the device referred to by the corresponding WWPN.

Description: The World-Wide Port Name to boot from.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be World-Wide Port Name (WWPN) to boot from.

Description: The active FCoE VLAN ID.
Normative Description: For FCoE connections, the value of this property shall be null or a VLAN ID currently being used for FCoE traffic.  When the FCoE link is down this value shall be null.  When the FCoE link is up this value shall be either the FCoELocalVLANId property or a VLAN discovered via the FIP protocol.

Description: The locally configured FCoE VLAN ID.
Normative Description: For FCoE connections, the value of this property shall be the VLAN ID configured locally by setting this property.  This value shall be used for FCoE traffic to this network device function during boot unless AllowFIPVLANDiscovery is true and a valid FCoE VLAN ID is found via the FIP VLAN Discovery Protocol.

Description: This is the permanent WWNN address assigned to this network device function (physical function).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the permanent World-Wide Node Name (WWNN) of this network device function (physical function). This value is typically programmed during the manufacturing time. This address is not assignable.

Description: This is the permanent WWPN address assigned to this network device function (physical function).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the permanent World-Wide Port Name (WWPN) of this network device function (physical function). This value is typically programmed during the manufacturing time. This address is not assignable.

Description: This is the currently configured WWNN address of the network device function (physical function).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the effective current World-Wide Node Name (WWNN) of this network device function (physical function). If an assignable WWNN is not supported, this is a read only alias of the PermanentWWNN.

Description: The configuration source of the WWNs for this connection (WWPN and WWNN).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the configuration source of the World-Wide Names (WWNs) for this connection (WWPN and WWNN).

Description: This is the currently configured WWPN address of the network device function (physical function).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the effective current World-Wide Port Name (WWPN) of this network device function (physical function). If an assignable WWPN is not supported, this is a read only alias of the PermanentWWPN.

Description: Uniquely identifies the resource within the collection of like resources.
Normative Description: This property represents an identifier for the resource.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification.

Description: iSCSI Boot.
Normative Description: This object shall contain iSCSI boot capabilities, status, and configuration values for this network device function.

Description: The iSCSI boot authentication method for this network device function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the iSCSI boot authentication method for this network device function.

Description: The shared secret for CHAP authentication.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the shared secret for CHAP authentication.

Description: The username for CHAP authentication.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall behe username for CHAP authentication.

Description: The IPv6 or IPv4 iSCSI boot default gateway.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IPv6 or IPv4 iSCSI boot default gateway.

Description: The IPv6 or IPv4 address of the iSCSI initiator.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IPv6 or IPv4 address of the iSCSI boot initiator.

Description: The iSCSI initiator name.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the iSCSI boot initiator name.  The value of this property should match formats defined in RFC3720 or RFC3721.

Description: The IPv6 or IPv4 netmask of the iSCSI boot initiator.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IPv6 or IPv4 netmask of the iSCSI boot initiator.

Description: The type of IP address (IPv6 or IPv4) being populated in the iSCSIBoot IP address fields.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall behe type of IP address (IPv6 or IPv4) being populated in the iSCSIBoot IP address fields.  Mixing of IPv6 and IPv4 addresses on the same network device function shall not be permissible.

Description: Whether the iSCSI boot initiator uses DHCP to obtain the iniator name, IP address, and netmask.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether the iSCSI boot initiator uses DHCP to obtain the iniator name, IP address, and netmask.

Description: The CHAP Secret for 2-way CHAP authentication.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the CHAP Secret for 2-way CHAP authentication.

Description: The CHAP Username for 2-way CHAP authentication.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the CHAP Username for 2-way CHAP authentication.

Description: The IPv6 or IPv4 address of the primary DNS server for the iSCSI boot initiator.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IPv6 or IPv4 address of the primary DNS server for the iSCSI boot initiator.

Description: The logical unit number (LUN) for the primary iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the logical unit number (LUN) for the primary iSCSI boot target.

Description: The IP address (IPv6 or IPv4) for the primary iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IP address (IPv6 or IPv4) for the primary iSCSI boot target.

Description: The name of the iSCSI primary boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the name of the primary iSCSI boot target.  The value of this property should match formats defined in RFC3720 or RFC3721.

Description: The TCP port for the primary iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the TCP port for the primary iSCSI boot target.

Description: This indicates if the primary VLAN is enabled.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be used to indicate if this VLAN is enabled for the primary iSCSI boot target.

Description: The 802.1q VLAN ID to use for iSCSI boot from the primary target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the 802.1q VLAN ID to use for iSCSI boot from the primary target.  This VLAN ID is only used if PrimaryVLANEnable is true.

Description: Whether IPv6 router advertisement is enabled for the iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether IPv6 router advertisement is enabled for the iSCSI boot target.  This setting shall only apply to IPv6 configurations.

Description: The IPv6 or IPv4 address of the secondary DNS server for the iSCSI boot initiator.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IPv6 or IPv4 address of the secondary DNS server for the iSCSI boot initiator.

Description: The logical unit number (LUN) for the secondary iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the logical unit number (LUN) for the secondary iSCSI boot target.

Description: The IP address (IPv6 or IPv4) for the secondary iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the IP address (IPv6 or IPv4) for the secondary iSCSI boot target.

Description: The name of the iSCSI secondary boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the name of the secondary iSCSI boot target.  The value of this property should match formats defined in RFC3720 or RFC3721.

Description: The TCP port for the secondary iSCSI boot target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the TCP port for the secondary iSCSI boot target.

Description: This indicates if the secondary VLAN is enabled.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be used to indicate if this VLAN is enabled for the secondary iSCSI boot target.

Description: The 802.1q VLAN ID to use for iSCSI boot from the secondary target.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the 802.1q VLAN ID to use for iSCSI boot from the secondary target.  This VLAN ID is only used if SecondaryVLANEnable is true.

Description: Whether the iSCSI boot target name, LUN, IP address, and netmask should be obtained from DHCP.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether the iSCSI boot target name, LUN, IP address, and netmask should be obtained from DHCP.

Description: The number of virtual functions (VFs) that are available for this Network Device Function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the number of virtual functions (VFs) that are available for this Network Device Function.

Description: The name of the resource or array element.
Normative Description: This object represents the Name property.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification. The value of this string shall be of the format for the reserved word *Name*.

Description: Capabilities of this network device function.
Normative Description: This object shall contain an array of capabilities of this network device function.

Description: Capabilities of this network device function.
The configured capability of this network device function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the configured capability of this network device function.

Description: This is the manufacturer/provider specific extension moniker used to divide the Oem object into sections.
Normative Description: The value of this string shall be of the format for the reserved word *Oem*.

Description: The physical port that this network device function is currently assigned to.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the physical port that this network device function is currently assigned to. This value shall be one of the AssignablePhysicalPorts array members.

Description: This type describes the status and health of a resource and its children.
Normative Description: This type shall contain any status or health properties of a resource.

Description: Whether Single Root I/O Virtualization (SR-IOV) Virual Functions (VFs) are enabled for this Network Device Function.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether Single Root I/O Virtualization (SR-IOV) Virual Functions (VFs) are enabled for this Network Device Function.

Description: The current ETag of the resource.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a string that is defined by the ETag HTTP header definition in RFC7232.

Description: Provides a description of this resource and is used for commonality  in the schema definitions.
Normative Description: This object represents the Description property.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification.

Description: Contains the members of this collection.
The name of the resource or array element.
Normative Description: This object represents the Name property.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification. The value of this string shall be of the format for the reserved word *Name*.

Description: This is the manufacturer/provider specific extension moniker used to divide the Oem object into sections.
Normative Description: The value of this string shall be of the format for the reserved word *Oem*.

Description: The available actions for this resource.
Normative Description: The Actions property shall contain the available actions for this resource.

Description: Network Port Active Link Technology.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the configured link technology of this port.

Description: The array of configured network addresses (MAC or WWN) that are associated with this Network Port, including the programmed address of the lowest numbered Network Device Function, the configured but not active address if applicable, the address for hardware port teaming, or other network addresses.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be an array of configured network addresses that are associated with this network port, including the programmed address of the lowest numbered network device function, the configured but not active address if applicable, the address for hardware port teaming, or other network addresses.

Description: Provides a description of this resource and is used for commonality  in the schema definitions.
Normative Description: This object represents the Description property.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification.

Description: Whether IEEE 802.3az Energy Efficient Ethernet (EEE) is enabled for this network port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether IEEE 802.3az Energy Efficient Ethernet (EEE) is enabled for this network port.

Description: The locally configured 802.3x flow control setting for this network port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the locally configured 802.3x flow control setting for this network port.

Description: The 802.3x flow control behavior negotiated with the link partner for this network port (Ethernet-only).
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the 802.3x flow control behavior negotiated with the link partner for this network port (Ethernet-only).

Description: Uniquely identifies the resource within the collection of like resources.
Normative Description: This property represents an identifier for the resource.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification.

Description: The status of the link between this port and its link partner.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the link status between this port and its link partner.

Description: The name of the resource or array element.
Normative Description: This object represents the Name property.  All values for resources described by this schema shall comply to the requirements as described in the Redfish specification. The value of this string shall be of the format for the reserved word *Name*.

Description: The array of maximum bandwidth allocation percentages for the Network Device Functions associated with this port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be an array of maximum bandwidth allocation percentages for the Network Device Functions associated with this port.

Description: The maximum bandwidth allocation percentage allocated to the corresponding network device function instance.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the maximum bandwidth percentage allocation for the associated network device function.

Description: Contains the members of this collection.
Normative Description: A Network Device Function represents a logical interface exposed by the network adapter.

Description: The array of minimum bandwidth allocation percentages for the Network Device Functions associated with this port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be an array of minimum bandwidth percentage allocations for each of the network device functions associated with this port.

Description: The minimum bandwidth allocation percentage allocated to the corresponding network device function instance.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the minimum bandwidth percentage allocation for the associated network device function.  The sum total of all minimum percentages shall not exceed 100.

Description: Contains the members of this collection.
Normative Description: A Network Device Function represents a logical interface exposed by the network adapter.

Description: This is the manufacturer/provider specific extension moniker used to divide the Oem object into sections.
Normative Description: The value of this string shall be of the format for the reserved word *Oem*.

Description: The physical port number label for this port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the physical port number on the network adapter hardware that this Network Port corresponds to.  This value should match a value visible on the hardware.  When HostPortEnabled and ManagementPortEnabled are both "false", the port shall not establish physical link.

Description: The largest maximum transmission unit (MTU) that can be configured for this network port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the largest maximum transmission unit (MTU) that can be configured for this network port.

Description: Whether or not the port has detected enough signal on enough lanes to establish link.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether the port has detected enough signal on enough lanes to establish link.

Description: This type describes the status and health of a resource and its children.
Normative Description: This type shall contain any status or health properties of a resource.

Description: The set of Ethernet capabilities that this port supports.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be an array of zero or more Ethernet capabilities supported by this port.

Description: The set of Ethernet capabilities that this port supports.
The self-described link capabilities of this port.
Normative Description: This object shall describe the static capabilities of the port, irrespective of transient conditions such as cabling, interface module presence, or remote link parter status or configuration.

Description: The self-described link network technology capabilities of this port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a network technology capability of this port.

Description: The speed of the link in Mbps when this link network technology is active.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be the speed of the link in megabits per second (Mbps) for this port when this link network technology is active.

Description: Whether Wake on LAN (WoL) is enabled for this network port.
Normative Description: The value of this property shall be a boolean indicating whether Wake on LAN (WoL) is enabled for this network port.
